Monks at Chion-in Temple practice ringing the giant Ogane Bell (cast in 1636), in preparation for the official bell ringing 108 times on New Year's Eve.
</p>

<p class="jp">   

知恩院の僧侶たちは、大鐘（1636年鋳造）を鳴らす練習をしている。大晦日には除夜の鐘が108回撞かれる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Higashiyama" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Monks at Chion-in Temple practice ringing the giant Ogane Bell (cast in 1636), in preparation for the official bell ringing 108 times on New Year's Eve.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05778.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05778.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ryoanji・龍安寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231226/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ryoanji・龍安寺" /><published>2023-12-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ryoanji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231226/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Late afternoon light casts shadows at Ryoanji Temple’s stone garden.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
龍安寺の石庭に影を落とす午後の光。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Late afternoon light casts shadows at Ryoanji Temple’s stone garden.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05618-brighterstill.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05618-brighterstill.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tenryuji Temple・天龍寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231224/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tenryuji Temple・天龍寺" /><published>2023-12-24T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-24T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tenryuji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231224/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Sogenchi Garden in the afternoon. Judicious framing and careful erasing eliminates the other temple visitors.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
午後の曹源池庭園。私は写真を慎重に額装しと、他の訪問者の一部を消した。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Tenryu-ji" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Sogenchi Garden in the afternoon. Judicious framing and careful erasing eliminates the other temple visitors.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05609.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05609.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama Mountain View・嵐山からの眺め</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231223/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama Mountain View・嵐山からの眺め" /><published>2023-12-23T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-23T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama-view</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231223/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Looking east across Kyoto from Daihikaku-ji Temple on a cold clear afternoon, you can see the Sagano Sightseeing Train (left) and visitors enjoying the Katsura (Oi) River in their blue rowboat.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
寒い晴れた日の午後、大悲閣寺から東の京都を眺めると、嵯峨野トロッコ列車（左）と大堰川（桂川）の手漕ぎボートの人が見える。</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Panoramas" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking east across Kyoto from Daihikaku-ji Temple on a cold clear afternoon, you can see the Sagano Sightseeing Train (left) and visitors enjoying the Katsura (Oi) River in their blue rowboat.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05590.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05590.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Central Exit・中央口</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231220/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Central Exit・中央口" /><published>2023-12-20T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-20T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/centralexit</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231220/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Travelers in bright colors pass through Kyoto Station.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
鮮やかな色彩の旅人が京都駅を通過する。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Travelers in bright colors pass through Kyoto Station.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_DSCF9379-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_DSCF9379-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Last Call for Fall・最後の秋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231217/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Last Call for Fall・最後の秋" /><published>2023-12-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ohara</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231217/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Some of the last maple leaves clinging to a tree, near Sanzen-in Temple.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
三千院の近くで、木にしがみついている最後の紅葉の一部。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Some of the last maple leaves clinging to a tree, near Sanzen-in Temple.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05525-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05525-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Sunrise・日の出</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231213/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sunrise・日の出" /><published>2023-12-13T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-13T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/sunrise</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231213/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Sun comes up over Kyoto’s eastern mountains in this photo taken from Arashiyama’s Togetsu bridge.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
嵐山の渡月橋から撮影した京都の東山から昇る太陽。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Sunrise" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Sun comes up over Kyoto’s eastern mountains in this photo taken from Arashiyama’s Togetsu bridge.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05280-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05280-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Fairy Tale・お伽話</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231210/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fairy Tale・お伽話" /><published>2023-12-10T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-10T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/fairytale</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231210/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Last light  (blue hour) in the Hozukyo Gorge. The Hoshinoya resort at left is illuminated for the evening, and so is the Sagano Scenic Railway on the right.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
保津峡の最後の明かり（ ブルーアワー )。左の星のやリゾートはライトアップされ、右の嵯峨野トロッコ線も照しされている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Night" /><category term="Lightup" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Last light (blue hour) in the Hozukyo Gorge. The Hoshinoya resort at left is illuminated for the evening, and so is the Sagano Scenic Railway on the right.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05231-2-bright.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05231-2-bright.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Japanese Bridge・反り橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231209/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Japanese Bridge・反り橋" /><published>2023-12-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/hashi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231209/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A small arched Japanese bridge at Osawa Ike Pond, from earlier this week.
</p>

<p class="jp">   
大沢池の小さな反り橋。今週初めに撮影。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Ponds" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A small arched Japanese bridge at Osawa Ike Pond, from earlier this week.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05215-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_A7R05215-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">15</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231208/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="15" /><published>2023-12-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-12-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/fifteen</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/231208/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The train platform at Shijo Omiya Station. I think the signs are the recommended speed (15km/hr). This is <em>not </em>the bullet train. 😉
</p>

<p class="jp">   
四条大宮駅のホーム。標識は推奨速度（時速15km）だと思う。
ここは新幹線ではない。😉
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The train platform at Shijo Omiya Station. I think the signs are the recommended speed (15km/hr). This is not the bullet train. 😉]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_DSCF9347.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2312_DSCF9347.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>